---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — LDR Visa"
  description="LDR Visa privacy policy — how we collect, use, and protect your information."
  noindex={true}
>
<style>
  .page-wrap {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }
  .page-header {
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin-bottom: .4rem;
  }
  .page-header p {
    color: #64748b;
    font-size: .9rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 2rem 0 .6rem;
  }
  p {
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: .95rem;
  }
  ul {
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: .95rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  li { margin-bottom: .35rem; }
  a { color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline; }
</style>

<div class="page-wrap">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: April 30, 2026</p>
  </div>

  <p>LDR Visa ("we," "us," or "our") operates the website ldrvisa.org (the "Site"). This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information in the following ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> When you visit the Site, we automatically collect standard log data including your IP address, browser type, pages visited, time spent on pages, and referring URLs. This is collected via analytics tools (such as Google Analytics).</li>
    <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to analyze traffic and improve the Site. You can control cookies through your browser settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Voluntarily provided information:</strong> If you contact us by email or through any contact form, we collect the information you choose to provide (such as your name and email address).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>We use the information collected to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Understand how visitors use the Site and improve our content</li>
    <li>Monitor and analyze traffic patterns and page performance</li>
    <li>Respond to inquiries or messages you send us</li>
    <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties.</p>

  <h2>3. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
  <p>We use Google Analytics to collect anonymized usage data. Google Analytics may set cookies on your device. You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.</p>
  <p>We may also use affiliate tracking cookies from partner programs (such as immigration service providers or financial tools). These cookies help us understand if you reached a partner's website through a link on our Site, which may result in us earning a commission at no additional cost to you.</p>

  <h2>4. Affiliate Links</h2>
  <p>Some links on this Site are affiliate links. If you click an affiliate link and make a purchase or sign up for a service, we may earn a commission. This does not affect the price you pay or our editorial independence. We only link to services we believe may be genuinely useful to our readers.</p>

  <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>Our Site may contain links to third-party websites, including U.S. government websites (USCIS, State Department), immigration service providers, and financial services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>We retain usage data collected through analytics tools for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, typically up to 26 months as configured in our analytics platform. If you contact us directly, we retain your correspondence for as long as necessary to resolve your inquiry.</p>

  <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>Our Site is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.</p>

  <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The right to access the personal information we hold about you</li>
    <li>The right to request correction of inaccurate data</li>
    <li>The right to request deletion of your data</li>
    <li>The right to opt out of analytics tracking</li>
    <li>California residents may have additional rights under the CCPA</li>
    <li>EU/EEA residents may have additional rights under the GDPR</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at the email address below.</p>

  <h2>9. Security</h2>
  <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the Site and any information you provide. However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

  <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: <a href="mailto:hello@ldrvisa.org">hello@ldrvisa.org</a></p>
</div>
</Base>
